Left a bad review for Chevy when I took my car in last week, and they called me back in like 30 mins. Trying to see if they'll install bluetooth auido for free to make up for it lol
Why was it a poor experience?

I'll start from the beginning with CarMax. The model I picked, normally doesn't come with remote start, but the one I got had it (not some 3rd party shit one, it was the actual chevy remote start for that car). but when I went to buy the car it wasn't working. the chick said maybe it was the cold (cuz this was when it was -50), and that I should try it agian in a few days and if it doesn't work they'll take care of it. So it never ended up working, took it in, and they tried some stuff with the key and weren't able to get it to work. So they said they'll have to look at the remote start mechanism and see why it's not working. so after about 30 mins they come back and say, the car doesn't have remote start installed in it lol
So why is it chevys fault lol

So they tell me it will have to be installed, so I ask how long that will take, and they say that they can't install it. Chevy has to install it themselves because it's an offical chevy remote start thing blah blah blah
So we setup an appointment with Chevy to get it in stalled, and it just so happens that my appointment day coincided with the last huge blizzard we had
So I call to see if they are still open, and that my appointment is still on, and i got the go ahead to come in, so I drive 30 mins to the shop in the blizzard, and drop off my car
they didn't know why i was there or anything about my appointment lol but eventually figured it out and told me I could wait in the waiting room until the work was done on my car

I'm in the waiting room for an hour (they said it could take up to 2 hours) and the guy comes in and is like "yeah we don't have the remote start part here in the shop..." and when I setup my appointment the girl specifically said the part had been ordered and would be ready when I came in
They said they'd call me when a part came in, should be very soon...
So i drive back home in the blizzard, after like 2 hours of being there, with zero progress made on my car lol
over a week later, and I never got a call from them
but I got an email saying "we see your service has been completed! tell us about your experience!" with a survey. So i took it and left a review with everything that happened to me lol
